    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-21T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-21T16:00:00-05:00" n="69"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/67<hi rend="superscript"
                    >14/25</hi>: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-21T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 21, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:53 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>199. Department’s telegram No. 133, August 4, 3 p.m. Conversations formally began
                    today and progressing favorably. Chilean participants General Escudero, Chief of
                    Staff of the Army, Admiral Daroch and Commander Mujica of [apparent omission],
                    no better men could possibly have been found. They are accompanied by four or
                    five assistants.</p>
                <p>Unhappily, the United Press correspondent here, the day before the meetings
                    began, displayed a telegram from United Press in the United States saying that
                    an Army officer was on the way here and to observe his movements. I have stoutly
                    disclaimed all knowledge of such visit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
